#include <bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

int main()
{
    ios_base::sync_with_stdio(false);
    cin.tie(0);
    cout.tie(0);

    int t;
    cin >> t;

    while (t--)
    {
        int n, m;
        cin >> n >> m;

        int arr[n];
        int count[(int)(1e5+1)] = {0};
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++)
        {
            cin >> arr[i];
            count[arr[i]]++;
        }

        for (int i = 1; i <= m; i++)
        {
            cout << count[i] << "\n";
        }
        
    }

    return 0;
}


Here is the plain text of the problem statement:

```text
Time Limit: 1 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description

Given 2 numbers N, M and an array A of N numbers. For every number from 1 to M, print how many times this number appears in this array.

Input Format

The first line contains T, the number of test cases.

For each test case:
- The first line contains two space separated integers N and M.
- The second line contains N space separated integers each denoting an element of the array A.

Output Format

Print M lines, the i-th line should contain the number of times that the number i appears in A.

Constraints

1 ≤ T ≤ 10
1 ≤ N, M ≤ 10^5
1 ≤ A[i] ≤ M

Sample Input 1

1
10 5
1 2 3 4 5 3 2 1 5 3

Sample Output 1

2
2
3
1
2

Note

Numbers from 1 to 5 appear in the array as follows:
- 1 appears 2 times in the array.
- 2 appears 2 times in the array.
- 3 appears 3 times in the array.
- 4 appears once in the array.
- 5 appears 2 times in the array.
```
